newsitem.title: PAKISTAN: Pakistani interbank market rates remain high.
newsitem.headline: Pakistani interbank market rates remain high.

text.p: Pakistan's interbank money market rates remained at high levels on Tuesday owing to a liquidity crunch, dealers said.
Bids were initially quoted at 16 and 17 percent and offers at 20 percent, one dealer at the Standard Chartered Bank said.

However, after a lack of interest from borrowers, offers came down to 17.5 and 18 percent, the dealer said. Major trades took place at these levels but the rates rose to 19 and 19.5 percent before the close.
